oups bind acrolein in the bladder, allowing effective excretion and prevention  of toxic effects.[A18570] In addition, Mesna binds to and detoxifies a urotoxic ifosfamide metabolite called 4-hydroxy-ifosfamide.', 'Mesna binds to and inactivates acrolein there by preventing or reducing bladder problems', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
