e, phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinase and adenylosuccinate synthetase.[A903,A180781] Acyclovir triphosphate has higher affinity for viral DNA polymerase than cellular DNA polymerase and incorporates into the DNA where the missing 2'' and 3'' carbons causes DNA chain termination.[A180757] In other cases acyclovir triphosphate competes so strongly for viral DNA polymerase that other bases cannot associate with the enzyme, inactivating it.[A180757]', 'Acyclovir is a deoxynucleoside analog that inhibits the action of viral DNA polymerase and DNA replication of different herpesvirus.[L7303,L7315,L7318,L7321,L7324,L7327] Acyclovir has a wide therapeutic window as overdose is rare in otherwise healthy patients.[L7315]', 'DrugBank', 0, 0, 0);
